The Government of Japan has announced that it will provide approximately $5 billion over the next five years to Afghanistan and will also fulfill its April 2009 pledge of $1 billion for economic assistance to Pakistan. The United States welcomes this announcement and appreciates Japan's efforts in assisting with the stabilization and reconstruction of Afghanistan. Japan is one of the largest bilateral donors in foreign assistance to Pakistan and Afghanistan, highlighting its leadership in the region. President Obama looks forward to renewing the alliance with Japan and discussing their ongoing partnership on Afghanistan, Pakistan, and other important bilateral issues during his upcoming visit to Japan.